sequenceDiagram
    participant F as URL Frontier<br/>(per-domain queues)
    participant W as Fetcher Worker
    participant DNS as DNS Cache
    participant Site as Target Site
    participant P as HTML Parser
    participant Seen as URL Seen<br/>(Bloom + KV)
    participant CSeen as Content Seen<br/>(SimHash)
    participant Arc as Page Archive<br/>(object store)

    W->>F: dequeue (domain whose<br/>next_fetch_time elapsed)
    F-->>W: url, depth
    W->>DNS: resolve(domain)
    DNS-->>W: ip (cached)
    W->>Site: GET url (robots.txt respected)
    alt fetch ok
        Site-->>W: html, headers
        W->>P: parse(html)
        P-->>W: links[], content
        W->>CSeen: simhash(content) seen?
        alt near-duplicate
            Note over W,CSeen: drop page<br/>(boilerplate/mirror)
        else novel content
            W->>Arc: PUT hash(url) -> page
            loop each extracted link
                W->>Seen: bloom check
                alt probably seen
                    Note over W,Seen: skip
                else maybe new
                    Seen->>Seen: KV confirm
                    alt confirmed new
                        W->>F: enqueue(link, depth+1)
                        W->>Seen: mark seen
                    end
                end
            end
        end
        W->>F: update next_fetch_time<br/>(per crawl_delay)
    else timeout / 5xx
        W->>F: requeue with backoff
    end
